uk.ac.ebi.gxa.loader
Class DefaultAtlasLoader

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ebi.gxa.loader.DefaultAtlasLoader
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean, AtlasLoader<URL>
public class DefaultAtlasLoader
extends Object
implements AtlasLoader<URL>, org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean

A default implementation of AtlasLoader that loads experiments and array designs referenced by URL. It can be configured with a URL pointing to the root path of all experiments, but this is not used - load operations should always be supplied with the full URL to the file to load.

Internally, this class uses an AtlasMAGETABLoader to perform all loading operations by default: as such, all experiments and array designs should be supplied in MAGE-TAB format.

Author:
Tony Burdett

getMissingDesignElementsCutoff

public double getMissingDesignElementsCutoff()
Description copied from interface: AtlasLoader
Gets the percentage of design elements that are allowed to be "missing" in the database before this load fails. Missing design elements occur when the data in the database excludes certain design elements that may be referenced in the data file supplied. This can happen for valid reasons: for example, control spots on an array are often not recorded in the database. This value sets the percentage of design elements that are referenced in the data file but NOT the database. If this percentage is exceeded in any particular load, it will fail.

Specified by:
getMissingDesignElementsCutoff in interface AtlasLoader<URL>
Returns:
the percentage of design elements that are allowed to be absent in the database before a load fails.

setMissingDesignElementsCutoff

public void setMissingDesignElementsCutoff(double missingDesignElementsCutoff)
Description copied from interface: AtlasLoader
Sets the percentage of design elements that are allowed to be "missing" in the database before this load fails. The percentage value - e.g. 0.25 - should be supplied here. Missing design elements occur when the data in the database excludes certain design elements that may be referenced in the data file supplied. This can happen for valid reasons: for example, control spots on an array are often not recorded in the database. This value sets the percentage of design elements that are referenced in the data file but NOT the database. If this percentage is exceeded in any particular load, it will fail.

AtlasLoaderService implementations should define sensible defaults for this cutoff - if it is not set here, the default for the service implementation will be used.

Specified by:

missingDesignElementsCutoff - the percentage of design elements that are allowed to be absent in the database before a load fails.

getAllowReloading

public boolean getAllowReloading()
Description copied from interface: AtlasLoader
Gets whether reloads are permissible by this loader. If true, experiments that are already present in the backing datasource will be reloaded unchecked (with an optional warning log statement). If false, attempting to reload an existing experiment will cause an exception to be thrown.

loadExperiment

public void loadExperiment(URL experimentResource)
Description copied from interface: AtlasLoader
Perform a load operation on a reference to a particular experiment resource

Note that this method is not guaranteed to be synchronous, it only guarantees that the load operation has started. Implementations are free to define their own multithreaded strategies for loading. If you wish to be notified on completion, you should register a listener to get callback events when the build completes by using AtlasLoader.loadExperiment(Object, uk.ac.ebi.gxa.loader.listener.AtlasLoaderListener). You can also use a listener to get at any errors that may have occurred during loading.

Specified by:
loadExperiment in interface AtlasLoader<URL>
Parameters:
experimentResource - the reference to the experiment you wish to load
